# Web dashboard build-time configuration (Vite).
# Copy to `web/.env` for local dev, or set these as build args in the container.

# Base URL for the PROXIMUS API.
# - Local dev default (unset): "/api", proxied to http://localhost:8000 by vite.
# - Docker/nginx: leave unset — nginx proxies /api to the api service.
# - Direct cross-origin: set an absolute URL, e.g. https://proximus.jonnymate.com/api
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api

# API key sent as the `X-API-Key` header on every request. Set this to match the
# backend's API_KEY when the API is key-protected (i.e. any public deployment).
# NOTE: this is embedded in the client bundle and is visible to anyone who can
# load the dashboard — gate the dashboard itself (e.g. Caddy basic-auth / IAP)
# for real access control; the key is defense-in-depth against unauthenticated
# scanners hitting the API directly.
# VITE_API_KEY=
